%header
  .container
    %a(href="https://github.com/tangosource/simple-ci" target='_github')
      %img(style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; border: 0;" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/github/ribbons/forkme_left_red_aa0000.png" alt="Fork me on GitHub")
    = link_to root_path do
      .simple-ci-logo
    %p
      A continuous integration tool for github ruby projects
      %br
      You can easily use simple CI to run your tests and almost config-free. Just write the url for your Github project (EG. https://github.com/user/ruby-project), edit your deployment script and run!

    = text_field_tag 'github_url', nil, class: 'github_url form-control', placeholder: 'https://github.com/path/to/project'
